\begin_layout Title
Status consumption and intertemporal substitution
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract

\shape italic
A model for status consumption is derived based on the framework for intertempor
al consumption choice in the presence of long-term assets.
 Status is endogenised as states of financial stability and included as
 part of the consumer's utility in the intertemporal model for substitution
 between quality in non-durable consumption and savings for future assets.
 
\end_layout

