\begin_layout Standard
The role of probability weighting functions also shows how a belief in unlikely
 jump 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma(\psi)$
\end_inset

 (e.g.
 more expenditure on status consumption) would have an influence on consumption.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Given the dynamics in the Equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:Bernoulli_dynamics"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, a consumer faces the asset choice 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{t+1}=A_{t}-\delta\psi+\sigma(\psi)X_{t}$
\end_inset

.
 Here, 
\begin_inset Formula $P(X_{t}=1)=p$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $P(X_{t}=0)=1-p$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi$
\end_inset

